The paper discusses the human-computer interaction in scientific research, which is a key aspect of the field of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI). The paper also focuses on the software aspect of scientific research, which falls under the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of mathematical equations in scientific models, which is related to the sub-category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). The paper also describes a proof-of-concept implementation of a digital scientific notation, which is related to the sub-category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the black-box nature of scientific software and the potential for mistakes, which is related to the sub-category of Scientific Computing (cs.SC).
